@startuml sq_mem01_persist_knowledge
' ============================================================
' Title:     MEM-01 — PERSIST Knowledge
' Boundary:  nasim code agent
' Purpose:   Store cross-session knowledge entries
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    docs/UC/README.md
' Review:    docs/audit/audit.2026.06.20.sq-sm-chain.car.md
' ============================================================

title nasim — MEM-01 PERSIST Knowledge

' Participants with box colors per C4 layer

note over participants
  Scope:          Knowledge persistence across sessions
  Preconditions:  MemoryStore initialized, scope valid
  Excludes:       Search and recall (MEM-02, MEM-03)
  Contexts:       Session checkpoint, learning capture
  Rollback:       Transactional write with rollback on index failure
  Design:         Append-only store with index synchronization
end note

== MEM-01 PERSIST Knowledge ==

AgentOrchestrator -> MemoryStore: persist(key, value, scope)
MemoryStore -> MemoryScope: validate_scope(scope)
MemoryScope --> MemoryStore: scope_valid
MemoryStore -> MemoryStore: write_to_disk(key, value)
MemoryStore -> MemoryIndex: index_entry(key, value, metadata)
MemoryIndex --> MemoryStore: indexed
MemoryStore --> AgentOrchestrator: persist_confirmed(key)

note over participants
  Flow:    Validate scope -> write disk -> index -> confirm
  State:   validating -> writing -> indexing -> persisted
  Failure: Disk write fails -> rollback, no index update
  Success: Entry persisted and indexed for search
end note

@enduml